lead_paragraph: Crews shored up levees at swollen rivers, stabilized slippery hillsides and tried to contain sewage and oil spills today as another El Nino-driven storm threatened to soak Southern California. Up to four and a half inches of rain is expected in some areas on Monday, the National Weather Service said.
abstract: Southern California braces for another El Nino-driven storm that is expected to bring up to four and a half inches of rain in some areas (S)

headline.main: National News Briefs; California Braces For the Next Storm
